fields.name: Kupka Karel Mr
fields.comments: Karel Kupka was a French ethnologist of Czech origin, who was a research officer with France's National Centre of Scientific Research. He started visiting Australian in the 1951, and later planned the Australian Arts room at the Museum of African and Oceanic Arts in Paris. He collected items in the early 1960s from Arnhem Land for various European Museums, and also collected a series of bark paintings for the Australian Institute of Aboriginal Studies which at one time were deposited at the Institute of Anatomy, Canberra. See UNESCO COURIER articles.

Ross William Father
fields.comments: 1895 - 1973. Catholic missionary sent to New Guinea in 1926 and worked in the Madang area.  He opened many new mission stations such as in the Adelbert Ranges (1927-1930), up the Ramu River (1931). Pioneer missionary in Mount Hagen area in 1934. His base of operations for 40 years was next to the Magei airstrip built by gold miners Mick and Dan Leahy.  Worked extensively with the Jiga, Yamuga, and Mogei clansmen.  IN 1976, the Postal Administration of PNG issues a 7t commemorative stamp.
